{meta: title Crying in the Deep Blue Sea}
{meta: artist Hank Thompson}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Well I went to see my baby [F]she said stay away from [C]me
[F]'Cause I'm a hot wire and you're a flat [C]tire
[G7]And I'm a-lettin' you go you [C]see
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Chorus
[F]And now I'm gone you can look for [C]me
[G7]Down by the ocean cryin' in the deep blue [C]sea
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
Well I never thought my baby would ever say goodbye
That goes to show that a man don't know
Just how the cards can lie
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
Repeat chorus
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
She left me here to weep and moan nothin' but the doggone blues
I've made my bid but she flipped her lid
And now I've got the walkin' shoes
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
Repeat Chorus
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
Well the tears I shed this mornin' and the tears I shed last night
I cried by gosh but it just can't wash
My baby from my sight
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 8}
Repeat Chorus
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 9}
When I looked out on the ocean Lord it was deep and wide
Well my baby's gone and I can't go on
So I hung my little head and cried
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 10}
Repeat chorus
{end_of_verse}
